**Class Based Components:-
 --class based component --Normal js class.
 --Syntax:-
class UserClass extends React.Component{
    render(){
        return(<div></div>)
    }
    }

--Class based has render () method which gives us jsx code.
-- React.Component import from react library.
-- to use props use:- constructor(props) {
    super(props);
    
  }
  --Super is used to mandatory while use props.
  --To call props in input use:- this.props.<parameter name>
   --When created class constructor is called and props is extracted.hence props use any where in code.

--To create state variable:-
    this.state = {
      count: 1,
    };

To use it:-  <h1>Count={this.state.count}</h1>

**Life cycle of class component:-
--parent constructor->parent render
--child constructor->child render
order of calling
 --constructor call 
 --render() method
  --componentDidMount() method


  **Life Cycle has two phases:
  1.Render phase:- -- component mounting,constructor calling,render method.
  2.Commit phase:- componentDidMount(),work with DOM,componentDidUpdate()

